    <solution><p>The radicand, <m>19\text{,}</m> is between <m>16</m> and <m>25\text{,}</m> so <m>\sqrt{19}</m> is between <m>\sqrt{16}</m> and <m>\sqrt{25}\text{,}</m> or between <m>4</m> and <m>5\text{.}</m> We notice that <m>19</m> is in the middle between <m>16</m> and <m>25</m> but closer to <m>16\text{.}</m> We estimate <m>\sqrt{19}</m> to be about <m>4.4\text{.}</m></p>
<p>We can check our estimate by calculating:</p>
<p><me>4.4^2=19.36</me></p>
<p>So <m>4.4^2</m> is close to <m>19\text{,}</m> and <m>4.4</m> is close to <m>\sqrt{19}\text{.}</m></p>
